               <head>Praedicator salutis (Latin translation of Isaac Abravanel's 'Mashmi῾a yeshu῾ah')</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85100947" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A Latin translation of Isaac Abravanel's 'Mashmi῾a yeshu῾ah'. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="la" otherLangs="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="425v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="la">Praedicator salutis</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Mashmi῾a yeshu῾ah</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">משמיע ישועה</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The translation was made from the Amsterdam edition of 1644, the title-page of which is also given. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The translation itself ends on folio 407r, the remaining leaves being occupied with notes headed 'Notae in Masmia Jeshua', and containing critical remarks in refutation of the argument of the text. This part is also in Latin, with the exception of folio 425, which is in French. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
